1
00:02:05,325 --> 00:02:08,385
It rained for months on end.

2
00:02:09,229 --> 00:02:12,198
The whole of Tokyo was flooded.

3
00:02:13,734 --> 00:02:16,235
The damage
ran to billions of yen,

4
00:02:16,236 --> 00:02:20,400
and the dead and missing
numbered in their millions.

5
00:02:20,541 --> 00:02:22,600
The survivors

6
00:02:22,743 --> 00:02:26,509
all mutated into
strange amphibian monsters,

7
00:02:26,647 --> 00:02:31,778
adapting quickly to the
suddenly changing climate.

8
00:02:31,919 --> 00:02:33,784
We're all going to die!

9
00:02:33,921 --> 00:02:37,483
No, we'll mutate.

10
00:02:37,826 --> 00:02:40,127
We mustn't breed!

11
00:02:40,128 --> 00:02:43,130
Think what the children
would look like.

12
00:02:43,131 --> 00:02:44,632
No, actually,

13
00:02:44,633 --> 00:02:47,500
the horniness is
part of the mutation.

14
00:02:47,636 --> 00:02:48,899
That's why the species
is so successful

15
00:02:49,038 --> 00:02:54,704
from an evolutionary
point of view.

16
00:02:55,244 --> 00:02:58,407
<i>- Hello?
- Hiroko, where are you?</i>

17
00:02:58,548 --> 00:03:00,549
No, we're not lost,

18
00:03:00,550 --> 00:03:02,351
just stuck in traffic.

19
00:03:02,352 --> 00:03:04,377
<i>- Where are you?
- Right now...</i>

20
00:03:06,122 --> 00:03:09,625
<i>- We've just passed Shinsencho.
- You're almost here.</i>

21
00:03:09,626 --> 00:03:11,927
<i>- OK, talk to you in a bit.
- OK.</i>

22
00:03:11,928 --> 00:03:13,929
Yeah, see you.

23
00:03:14,131 --> 00:03:17,133
Are we going the right way?

24
00:03:17,534 --> 00:03:20,196
Look at the map.

25
00:03:24,842 --> 00:03:25,809
Sorry.

26
00:03:26,744 --> 00:03:27,711
Sorry.

27
00:03:38,524 --> 00:03:42,483
We're already... there,
I think.

28
00:03:42,628 --> 00:03:44,892
<i>Really?</i>

29
00:03:45,029 --> 00:03:47,191
<i>Where? What color is your car?</i>

30
00:03:47,333 --> 00:03:50,996
It's silver.

31
00:03:51,136 --> 00:03:52,398
A Honda.

32
00:03:52,838 --> 00:03:55,103
Well,
more like gray, really.

33
00:03:56,442 --> 00:03:59,207
<i>I've got a red umbrella.</i>

34
00:04:00,146 --> 00:04:01,408
A red umbrella?

35
00:04:02,548 --> 00:04:03,811
Spin it round.

36
00:04:04,251 --> 00:04:05,809
<i>I'll try.</i>

37
00:04:05,952 --> 00:04:09,683
<i>I'm spinning it, I'm spinning it.
Can't you see me?</i>

38
00:04:09,823 --> 00:04:12,007
Now jump.

39
00:04:12,325 --> 00:04:15,988
<i>Jump? OK, here I go...</i>

40
00:04:16,631 --> 00:04:19,394
Now on one leg.

41
00:04:22,436 --> 00:04:24,404
- Akemi!
- Hiroko!

42
00:04:34,349 --> 00:04:38,012
- Here, towels.
- Thanks.

43
00:04:43,825 --> 00:04:45,486
In Tokyo...

44
00:04:45,627 --> 00:04:48,892
the bigger the
company you work for...

45
00:04:49,031 --> 00:04:51,592
the smaller
the flat you get.

46
00:04:52,434 --> 00:04:54,801
You should work
for a smaller company.

47
00:04:55,337 --> 00:04:59,399
My company's
already pretty small.

48
00:05:01,344 --> 00:05:04,108
- It's a nice place.
- You think so?

49
00:05:04,248 --> 00:05:06,307
You still have Saburo, then?

50
00:05:07,550 --> 00:05:09,017
Little Saburo!

51
00:05:09,952 --> 00:05:13,411
It's raining tonight,
so your car should be OK.

52
00:05:13,557 --> 00:05:15,458
But you can't leave it.

53
00:05:15,459 --> 00:05:18,516
There's a hardware store

54
00:05:18,517 --> 00:05:21,897
just over there. Park in front...
It's been closed for a while.

55
00:05:32,544 --> 00:05:35,308
<i>AKEMI SHIMIZU</i>

56
00:05:36,548 --> 00:05:40,006
Now for this week's episode
of 'Where Are They Now? '

57
00:05:40,151 --> 00:05:42,813
Akira, what are you doing now?

58
00:05:43,655 --> 00:05:46,523
Well... I'm a filmmaker.

59
00:05:46,659 --> 00:05:50,095
He's just made a film
that he's showing around.

60
00:05:50,229 --> 00:05:52,390
The film's about...

61
00:05:52,531 --> 00:05:56,294
...is the main thing.
Please go and see it.

62
00:05:57,136 --> 00:05:58,194
This is it.

63
00:05:58,337 --> 00:06:06,403
But this is...
a porno theater.

64
00:06:08,347 --> 00:06:10,714
It's a real theater, then!

65
00:06:10,851 --> 00:06:13,115
It'll be dark and quiet.

66
00:06:14,354 --> 00:06:18,118
You shouldn't have cut
my sex scene after all!

67
00:06:18,959 --> 00:06:22,327
Are you making pornos?

68
00:06:23,029 --> 00:06:25,692
No, that was a joke.

69
00:06:26,334 --> 00:06:29,998
I had a part for Hiroko,
but she turned it down.

70
00:06:30,138 --> 00:06:32,504
What a pity. No ambition!

71
00:06:32,640 --> 00:06:36,303
Right!
That's her problem exactly.

72
00:06:36,444 --> 00:06:39,413
Why did you pass up
the chance to be a star?

73
00:06:39,748 --> 00:06:42,808
I don't like the sound
of my own voice.

74
00:06:42,951 --> 00:06:44,508
It sounds like this.

75
00:06:44,653 --> 00:06:47,918
I can't wait to see it.

76
00:06:48,056 --> 00:06:49,717
- Really?
- Yes.

77
00:06:49,858 --> 00:06:51,622
How about now?

78
00:06:51,760 --> 00:06:54,628
- I've got the DVD here.
- She might be tired.

79
00:06:54,764 --> 00:06:59,292
No, let's watch it now.
It's not too intellectual, is it?

80
00:07:01,938 --> 00:07:04,998
<i>There are so many lives
in the future.</i>

81
00:07:08,445 --> 00:07:12,313
<i>Assuming we haven't
destroyed ourselves first</i>

82
00:07:13,050 --> 00:07:16,507
<i>we could live on
after the end of the solar system.</i>

83
00:07:16,653 --> 00:07:21,318
<i>In the infinity
of new souls created</i>

84
00:07:22,359 --> 00:07:26,626
<i>there's no reason that one
shouldn't be me again.</i>

85
00:07:45,550 --> 00:07:47,109
Sorry.

86
00:07:49,554 --> 00:07:52,614
I have to get up early
in the morning.

87
00:07:54,360 --> 00:07:57,227
- Can you help me with this?
- This?

88
00:07:57,363 --> 00:08:01,026
I liked the bit I saw, though.

89
00:08:01,968 --> 00:08:03,902
You can change in
the bathroom.

90
00:08:05,137 --> 00:08:07,401
Hiroko, can you pull that side?

91
00:08:11,143 --> 00:08:14,447
I hope you'll be all right.
I'm sorry it's so cramped.

92
00:08:14,448 --> 00:08:15,813
It's fine.

93
00:08:15,949 --> 00:08:19,407
'A good soldier must suffer
with pride,' right?

94
00:08:20,053 --> 00:08:24,514
'Enduring the unendurable.
Suffering the... '

95
00:08:24,658 --> 00:08:26,717
Stop it, stupid!

96
00:08:29,564 --> 00:08:31,828
Seriously, though. Thanks.

97
00:08:31,966 --> 00:08:35,169
We'll start looking for
an apartment tomorrow.

98
00:08:35,771 --> 00:08:40,003
My boyfriend's staying next
Sunday. He's driving from Nagoya.

99
00:08:41,644 --> 00:08:45,603
His uncle works in advertising.

100
00:08:45,748 --> 00:08:48,012
Shall I ask him
to come and see your film?

101
00:08:48,150 --> 00:08:51,813
You think
he'd come from Nagoya?

102
00:08:51,954 --> 00:08:54,155
Of course not!
That's my side.

103
00:08:54,156 --> 00:08:56,358
His uncle lives in Tokyo.

104
00:08:56,359 --> 00:08:57,417
I'm switching it off.

105
00:08:57,560 --> 00:08:59,529
All that way, for your movie!

106
00:08:59,662 --> 00:09:02,632
Three, two, one...

107
00:09:02,765 --> 00:09:04,631
- Good night!
- Good night.

108
00:09:04,768 --> 00:09:07,670
Don't forget
to move your car tomorrow.

109
00:09:07,671 --> 00:09:09,298
The fines are huge.

110
00:09:15,345 --> 00:09:17,210
I'm glad it's raining.

111
00:09:48,347 --> 00:09:52,511
<i>Don't forget to move your car</i>

112
00:10:04,263 --> 00:10:05,321
Look.

113
00:10:06,265 --> 00:10:08,028
We'll be OK until Friday.

114
00:10:10,671 --> 00:10:13,138
<i>CLOSED UNTIL FRIDAY
NOVEMBER 16TH</i>

115
00:10:14,875 --> 00:10:19,029
What are you doing?
It'll go up if we don't pay.

116
00:10:19,146 --> 00:10:22,206
We're not kids anymore.

117
00:10:22,750 --> 00:10:24,912
Cover me!
I'm going into the safe!

118
00:10:27,454 --> 00:10:28,614
Copy that!

119
00:10:29,556 --> 00:10:33,617
We can't make any more mistakes.
Our budget's tight as it is.

120
00:10:36,565 --> 00:10:40,729
To rent an apartment...
Say the rent is 30,000...

121
00:10:40,869 --> 00:10:44,738
We'd need a deposit
of two months' rent.

122
00:10:46,776 --> 00:10:48,437
In all, we'd need...

123
00:10:49,144 --> 00:10:51,511
We would need
400,000 yen in advance.

124
00:10:57,753 --> 00:11:00,415
It's a good place
for young couples.

125
00:11:15,972 --> 00:11:18,031
Who are you? Let me out!

126
00:11:18,175 --> 00:11:21,042
It's popular with young couples.

127
00:11:21,178 --> 00:11:23,010
Do you like the view?

128
00:11:23,648 --> 00:11:25,809
Nice dead cat.

129
00:11:27,251 --> 00:11:29,719
Something smells like shit!

130
00:11:29,854 --> 00:11:32,015
I can't live in a dump like that.

131
00:11:34,059 --> 00:11:37,426
There wasn't any soap left
in Akemi's place.

132
00:11:38,363 --> 00:11:40,923
Do you think it's a hotel?

133
00:11:41,666 --> 00:11:43,532
I didn't mean that.

134
00:11:43,669 --> 00:11:46,035
My bad. Let's go and
buy some soap now.

135
00:11:48,674 --> 00:11:51,336
What's wrong? Are you mad?

136
00:11:52,277 --> 00:11:53,939
It's nothing.

137
00:11:54,079 --> 00:11:55,809
Come on, what is it?

138
00:11:57,149 --> 00:12:00,312
You said I have no ambition.

139
00:12:01,755 --> 00:12:02,915
What?

140
00:12:04,557 --> 00:12:09,017
Yesterday. You said
I have no ambition at all.

141
00:12:10,264 --> 00:12:12,026
I said that?

142
00:12:12,466 --> 00:12:15,923
It's not true.
I like photography and art.

143
00:12:16,070 --> 00:12:19,938
I've got a boating license,
and I read a lot too.

144
00:12:21,976 --> 00:12:25,639
But they're hobbies.
They're not the same as ambitions.

145
00:12:25,781 --> 00:12:27,145
What's the difference?

146
00:12:27,581 --> 00:12:29,208
You have to be able to define...

147
00:12:29,350 --> 00:12:33,014
who you are in the world
by what you do.

148
00:12:33,155 --> 00:12:38,218
What I like to do
defines who I am.

149
00:12:38,360 --> 00:12:40,420
Doesn't that make me
a richer person?

150
00:12:40,562 --> 00:12:43,827
You still have to be better at it
than others.

151
00:12:45,066 --> 00:12:46,931
Something's wrong.

152
00:12:50,573 --> 00:12:52,438
Something's wrong
with these buildings.

153
00:12:53,176 --> 00:12:55,736
They refuse all physical contact
with each other.

154
00:12:57,079 --> 00:13:01,039
You're always
say something clever

155
00:13:01,184 --> 00:13:03,753
to avoid really talking.

156
00:13:03,754 --> 00:13:08,520
Every night, flat ghosts
slide in and out of these gaps.

157
00:13:09,159 --> 00:13:10,523
And wander about the city...

158
00:13:14,364 --> 00:13:16,366
They wander about the city,

159
00:13:16,767 --> 00:13:19,031
scaring the people shitless.

160
00:13:20,070 --> 00:13:22,631
The authorities
fill in the gaps with concrete,

161
00:13:22,773 --> 00:13:24,934
but the buildings
keep moving apart,

162
00:13:25,777 --> 00:13:28,554
letting the flat creatures
take over.

163
00:13:32,483 --> 00:13:34,246
I could make them
out of paper.

164
00:13:38,958 --> 00:13:42,018
All right, what's the matter?

165
00:13:43,062 --> 00:13:45,040
I'm listening.

166
00:13:45,264 --> 00:13:47,365
I'm ready
for a dramatic conversation.

167
00:13:47,366 --> 00:13:49,425
with flashbacks
and a big climax...

168
00:13:49,569 --> 00:13:51,832
You've stopped
listening already.

169
00:13:51,971 --> 00:13:54,440
You're the one who's 'dramatic'!

170
00:13:57,276 --> 00:13:58,837
I'm listening.

171
00:14:01,981 --> 00:14:04,750
But we're talking a lot.

172
00:14:05,886 --> 00:14:08,764
That's not true!

173
00:14:24,071 --> 00:14:25,436
Maybe you're right.

174
00:14:27,475 --> 00:14:30,035
I don't think I know
what I'm doing.

175
00:14:30,779 --> 00:14:34,043
What, here?

176
00:14:34,181 --> 00:14:36,946
No, in general.

177
00:14:43,358 --> 00:14:45,660
You take things too seriously.

178
00:14:45,661 --> 00:14:48,526
Where's your sense of humor?

179
00:14:56,172 --> 00:14:58,436
There are
these two poisonous snakes.

180
00:15:00,276 --> 00:15:03,143
One says to the other.

181
00:15:04,682 --> 00:15:07,947
'We're poisonous, aren't we? '

182
00:15:08,585 --> 00:15:11,554
So the other one says

183
00:15:11,689 --> 00:15:14,749
'Of course we are.
Why do you ask? '

184
00:15:15,859 --> 00:15:19,727
And the first snake says

185
00:15:19,863 --> 00:15:23,731
'I've just bitten my tongue! '

186
00:15:37,382 --> 00:15:41,341
<i>PART-TIME JOB AVAILABLE
WRAPPING PURCHASES</i>

187
00:15:41,486 --> 00:15:42,453
A part-time job.

188
00:15:43,589 --> 00:15:45,351
We could work here.

189
00:15:45,490 --> 00:15:47,458
No, they'll pay peanuts!

190
00:15:47,994 --> 00:15:51,062
It'd take two weeks
to pay off the parking fine!

191
00:15:51,063 --> 00:15:53,224
Wait till you find a real job.

192
00:15:53,367 --> 00:15:54,833
I want to keep busy.

193
00:15:54,967 --> 00:15:58,069
Anyway, I have no ambition.

194
00:15:58,070 --> 00:16:01,836
so it's a perfectjob for me.
Come on!

195
00:16:20,293 --> 00:16:22,819
I did it without thinking
and got the job.

196
00:16:22,964 --> 00:16:24,226
Only you, Akira?

197
00:16:24,364 --> 00:16:27,334
But Hiroko's dog was great.

198
00:16:27,468 --> 00:16:29,026
They are stupid.

199
00:16:29,170 --> 00:16:30,536
It wasn't great.

200
00:16:30,671 --> 00:16:31,933
And it was a cat.

201
00:16:33,274 --> 00:16:36,176
You're better off
doing something else.

202
00:16:36,177 --> 00:16:37,878
I won't work there long.

203
00:16:37,879 --> 00:16:40,440
How long do you
plan to stay here?

204
00:16:42,684 --> 00:16:47,144
- We haven't really...
- We saw a nice place today.

205
00:16:47,289 --> 00:16:50,349
We have a good chance
of getting it.

206
00:16:52,996 --> 00:16:55,361
Yes, a really good chance!

207
00:16:56,066 --> 00:16:57,226
Where?

208
00:17:01,171 --> 00:17:02,638
Tokyo...

209
00:17:49,989 --> 00:17:52,390
No boyfriends, no pets.

210
00:17:52,391 --> 00:17:54,653
Is there anyone
who actually checks?

211
00:18:04,071 --> 00:18:06,538
Don't wrap two together.

212
00:18:09,675 --> 00:18:10,642
Hello.

213
00:18:18,285 --> 00:18:23,747
There seem to be some residents
already living here!

214
00:19:15,879 --> 00:19:18,041
<i>FRIDAY NOVEMBER 16TH</i>

215
00:19:19,684 --> 00:19:22,346
<i>CLOSED UNTIL FRIDAY
NOVEMBER 16TH</i>

216
00:19:42,874 --> 00:19:46,538
<i>CAR No 55M46-51 TOWED AWAY
TO MUNICIPAL POUND</i>

217
00:19:49,482 --> 00:19:53,748
So I wrap nine boxes
with just one roll of paper.

218
00:19:53,885 --> 00:19:56,588
But she says I should do eleven.

219
00:19:56,589 --> 00:19:59,649
How am I supposed to do that?
Even ten is impossible.

220
00:20:01,394 --> 00:20:02,656
What's the matter?

221
00:20:03,296 --> 00:20:06,061
The car was stolen today.

222
00:20:06,200 --> 00:20:07,359
What?

223
00:20:09,203 --> 00:20:11,262
All our equipment was in it.

224
00:20:11,905 --> 00:20:13,668
What about the screening?

225
00:20:15,209 --> 00:20:16,576
I'm screwed!

226
00:20:16,577 --> 00:20:18,579
No, you're not.

227
00:20:18,779 --> 00:20:22,943
Yesterday, I moved everything
into the apartment.

228
00:20:23,083 --> 00:20:25,552
I didn't like leaving it out there.

229
00:20:25,687 --> 00:20:28,951
Akemi was upset
so I forgot to tell you.

230
00:20:30,492 --> 00:20:32,153
Great thinking!

231
00:20:33,895 --> 00:20:35,760
The smoke machine too?

232
00:20:39,601 --> 00:20:43,662
I just told you.
There's the 15,000-yen fine

233
00:20:43,806 --> 00:20:47,109
plus a 14,000-yen towing fee.

234
00:20:47,410 --> 00:20:51,938
I don't have 29,000 yen. But
I need my things from the car.

235
00:20:52,481 --> 00:20:57,545
Can you take me to it
so I can get my stuff?

236
00:20:57,688 --> 00:21:00,748
Not until you pay the money.

237
00:21:00,891 --> 00:21:02,859
We're open until six.

238
00:21:02,992 --> 00:21:04,756
It's still my car!

239
00:21:04,895 --> 00:21:07,955
Not until you pay the money,
it's not.

240
00:21:09,900 --> 00:21:13,358
Let's just say
there's 29,000 yen in the car.

241
00:21:15,206 --> 00:21:18,108
If you just show me where it is

242
00:21:18,109 --> 00:21:20,810
I can get
the money and pay you.

243
00:21:20,811 --> 00:21:22,374
What do you say?

244
00:21:32,290 --> 00:21:34,953
What'll happen to it
if I don't pay?

245
00:22:38,794 --> 00:22:41,262
Make? Color?

246
00:22:41,396 --> 00:22:42,864
Year?

247
00:22:44,499 --> 00:22:45,660
Thank you.

248
00:22:45,802 --> 00:22:48,361
I hate him. He's a cavity!

249
00:22:49,705 --> 00:22:51,070
He's got bad teeth?

250
00:22:51,207 --> 00:22:54,267
No, I mean he's a cavity himself.

251
00:22:54,410 --> 00:22:56,379
Last year
he caught pneumonia.

252
00:22:56,512 --> 00:23:00,047
Too bad,
he has a good doctor!

253
00:23:05,087 --> 00:23:06,350
All that stuff?

254
00:23:11,595 --> 00:23:13,756
Here you go!
Put it in here, please.

255
00:23:13,898 --> 00:23:16,365
Where shall I put this?

256
00:23:47,500 --> 00:23:48,660
Look!

257
00:24:04,718 --> 00:24:07,881
<i>There are so many lives
in the future.</i>

258
00:24:16,697 --> 00:24:20,063
<i>Assuming we haven't
